HEADWORD: Cyclas
<hw>Cy"clas</hw> <pr>(s?"kl?s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Ciclatoun</er>.]</ety> <def>A long gown or surcoat (cut off in
front), worn in the Middle Ages. It was sometimes embroidered or
interwoven with gold. Also, a rich stuff from which the gown was
made.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

